quran[25]{c,v,t,f}:
  69,52,"So exalt the name of your Lord, the Most Great."
  74,31,"And We have not made the keepers of the Fire except angels. And We have not made their number except as a trial for those who disbelieve - that those who were given the Scripture will be convinced and those who have believed will increase in faith and those who were given the Scripture and the believers will not doubt and that those in whose hearts is disease [i.e., hypocrisy] and the disbelievers will say, "
  74,32,"No! By the moon."
  74,33,"And [by] the night when it departs."
  75,28,"And he [i.e., the dying one] is certain that it is the [time of] separation"
  75,29,"And the leg is wound about the leg,{1}",footnotes:1:[From the difficulties the person faces at death or his sudden awareness of the realities of both this world and the Hereafter.  It may also refer to his shrouding after death.]
  75,30,"To your Lord, that Day, will be the procession.{1}",footnotes:1:[Literally, "driving" or "herding" or "the place to which one is driven."]
  76,22,"[And it will be said], "
  76,23,"Indeed, it is We who have sent down to you, [O Muḥammad], the Qur’ān progressively."
  76,24,"So be patient for the decision of your Lord and do not obey from among them a sinner or ungrateful [disbeliever]."
  77,19,"Woe, that Day, to the deniers."
  77,20,"Did We not create you from a liquid disdained?"
  77,21,"And We placed it in a firm lodging [i.e., the womb]"
  78,16,"And gardens of entwined growth."
  78,17,"Indeed, the Day of Judgement is an appointed time -"
  78,18,"The Day the Horn is blown and you will come forth in multitudes"
  79,10,"They are [presently] saying, "
  79,11,"Even if we should be decayed bones?",footnotes:1:[The disbelievers say this in ridicule of the warning.]
  79,12,"They say, ",footnotes:1:[i.e., "If that were so, we would not be able to escape punishment."]
  80,7,"And not upon you [is any blame] if he will not be purified.{1}",footnotes:1:[The Prophet (ﷺ) was responsible only for conveying the message, not for ultimate guidance.]
  80,8,"But as for he who came to you striving [for knowledge]"
  80,9,"While he fears [Allāh],"
  81,4,"And when full-term she-camels{1} are neglected",footnotes:1:[Those ten months pregnant and nearing delivery. This verse alludes to distraction from the most valued of possessions.]
  81,5,"And when the wild beasts are gathered"
  81,6,"And when the seas are filled with flame{1}",footnotes:1:[Or "when the seas have overflowed [into each other]."]
